parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or seize, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the engine makes a loud noise or grinding sound
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on
blue smoke is visible from the exhaust
the engine oil light comes on
the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or seize, and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the oil light comes on
the vehicle smokes from the exhaust
the engine makes a loud noise or grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and power brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls randomly while traveling at low speeds
the engine shuts off
and the power steering and power brakes are disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal/steering column can cause smoke to emanate from the steering column, creating a fire hazard, and can also lead to loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The turn signal lever starts ticking and smoking
the turn signal switch continues clicking when the turn is completed
and smoke comes from the left front vent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery/alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and power brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery dies
the alternator fails
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can cause the air bag warning light to flicker and remain illuminated, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The air bag warning light flickers and remains illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pressure switch can cause the engine to leak oil, creating a fire hazard, and can lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The oil light begins to flicker
and oil leaks onto the top engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the speedometer can cause the vehicle's speed to be misreported, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer shows a different speed than GPS devices.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose
the steering wheel moves excessively
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fluid leaks
the power steering pump fails
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the vehicle loses power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The multi-stalk switch smokes and clicks
the signal lights stick on
the check engine light and oil light come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to stall can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls suddenly
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.
